Cross-border firing along LoC in Poonch 
9-3-2017 
Cross-border firing was witnessed on Thursday along the Line of Control (LoC) in Poonch district of Jammu and Kashmir.

Read more | Soldier found dead under ‘mysterious circumstances’ in Poonch

There was cross-border firing from 1330 to 1340 hours along the LoC in the Poonch sector, a district police officer said.

According to reports, one jawan has been injured in the firing.

However, the army has not yet issued a statement on the incident. A senior officer at the Northern Command said that they were checking the details. 
